The paper deals with random geometric graphs, which are a common topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the connectivity threshold of these graphs, which is a topic in network analysis (cs.SI) and algorithms (cs.NA). Finally, the paper applies the results to the geometric block model, which is a topic in machine learning and data analysis (cs.GT).
